data.title: Cadiz province, towns, villages, beaches – Travel guide, facts, maps
data.meta_description: Discover Cadiz Province in Andalusia, Cadiz city, the white villages, sherry from Jerez, the stunning beaches of Tarifa with its wind surfing culture.
data.text:
Discover the ancient coastal city of Cadiz

Cadiz is one of Costa de la Luz' oldest & most impressive cities. Beautiful sunsets, white beaches, and historic monuments will take your breath away

Cycling the Via Verde de la Sierra, Cadiz - Seville

Cycling the award winning Via Verde de la Sierra makes a fantastic day out for the whole family.

Hidden Cádiz No.1- Castillo de Castellar

A series of glimpses into some of the least known and most enchanting corners of Cádiz province.

Top 10 bars not to miss in Jerez and Cadiz's sherry country

To enjoy sherry in its natural habitat, get out of the bodegas.

Best sunset on the Costa de la Luz, Playa el Palmar

Looking for somewhere small, somewhere low key, somewhere that still hasn't been exploited by mass tourism? the village of El Palmar could be the answer

Zoo de Castellar - A Different Kind of Zoo

Everybody loves zoos. Does everybody love zoos? Zoos are good to keep children entertained and also to aid endangered species.

Setenil de las Bodegas, Cádiz

A rock formation, like a great wart on the side of a beautiful Spanish village. It is to be marvelled, if you wish to do so have a read of this.

A Living Nativity - Arcos de la Frontera

Enjoy the festivities of the Christmas period at a village sat precariously atop a sandstone ridge. Read on to discover more about the living belen!
